enchive
------------------------------------------
Enchive is a tool to encrypt files to yourself for long-term archival. It's a
focused, simple alternative to more complex solutions such as GnuPG or
encrypted filesystems. Enchive has no external dependencies and is trivial to
build for local use. Portability is emphasized over performance.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  libcurve25519-donna1-1.3-1bl4

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libcurve25519-donna-devel-1.3-1bl4
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/skeeto/enchive

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/skeeto/enchive/archive/refs/tags/3.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack enchive-3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./enchive-3.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/enchive-3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/enchive-3.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(enchive)
  /usr/bin/enchive.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/enchive.README
  /usr/share/doc/enchive/NEWS.md
  /usr/share/doc/enchive/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/enchive.1.gz

